						<summary>

						<p>Two sides of a slab in the Hādi-Paramēśvari temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record seems to register a grant of land to a person probably in connection with water management. It mentions God Kumara Swamy, the place Bijavūra, two <hi rend="italic">samantas</hi> and a <hi rend="italic">nāḍa-dhore.</hi> In the imprecatory section we find the mention of a hundred-<hi rend="italic">agnihōtrinūrbar-agnihōtrigaḷ.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
